Question 1
Prof says make a chart.

title: Kennedy Spann
text:
Connected to base (Python 3.12.7)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

data = {'A': 10, 'B': 15, 'C': 7}
names = list(data.keys())
values = list(data.values())

plt.bar(names, values)
plt.title('Simple Bar Chart')
plt.show()
